# Smart Agriculture Process Mode Deploy Workflow

Follow this rule when the task involves deploying, restarting localhost services, or verifying `ai.luyaxiang.com` using process mode.

## Current Topology (Process Mode)

- Domain: `ai.luyaxiang.com`
- Frontdoor: `cloudflared -> nginx 127.0.0.1:5173 -> Next web 127.0.0.1:3000 -> Python Agent 127.0.0.1:18010`
- Agent port: `.runtime/local-agent-port`, default `18010`
- Repo root: `/Users/mac/Desktop/gago-cloud/code/smart-agriculture`

## Required Workflow

1. Inspect the current state.
   - `git status`
   - Check ports `3000`, `5173`, `18010` with `lsof`
   - `docker ps`

2. Stop Docker containers if running for this project.
   ```bash
   docker compose --env-file .env -f infra/docker/docker-compose.yml stop agent web
   ```
   Never stop `cloudflared`, `nginx`, or unrelated containers.

3. Update code safely.
   - Check for local changes before `git pull`
   - Reinstall dependencies only when they changed
   - Rebuild web: `npm run build:web`

4. Restart process-mode services.
   - Agent: kill existing `uvicorn` owned by this repo → `bash scripts/dev/start-local-agent.sh`
   - Web: kill existing `next-server` on `3000` owned by this repo → `bash scripts/dev/start-local-web.sh`
   - Never kill `nginx` or `cloudflared`.

5. Verify localhost, then domain.
   - `curl http://localhost:3000/api/health`
   - `curl http://localhost:${LOCAL_AGENT_PORT}/health`
   - login + `POST /api/agent/chat` smoke
   - `curl https://ai.luyaxiang.com/api/health`
   - login + `POST https://ai.luyaxiang.com/api/agent/chat` smoke

## Never Do These

- Do not use Docker to start services — use `deploy-docker` rule instead.
- Do not restart `nginx` or `cloudflared`.
- Do not stop at `/api/health`; full verification requires login + chat smoke.
- Do not treat `ai.yaxianglu.com` as the target domain.
